WEBVTT

NOTE
English captions for "Beyond the Lens"
This file provides synchronized captions for accessibility

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:15.000
Every photograph tells a story.
Every frame captures a moment.
This is Beyond the Lens.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:35.000
SARAH KIM: When I pick up a camera,
I'm not just recording what I see.
I'm translating emotion, context, and humanity
into a visual language that transcends words.

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:52.000
NARRATOR: Sarah Kim has spent the last decade
documenting social movements through her lens,
creating powerful visual narratives
that have sparked conversations around the globe.

00:00:52.000 --> 00:01:15.000
MARCUS THOMPSON: The streets are my canvas.
Every corner, every face, every shadow
tells a different story.
My job is to be present enough
to capture those fleeting moments of truth.

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:32.000
NARRATOR: Marcus's work in urban photography
has been featured in major galleries worldwide,
bringing attention to the beauty and complexity
of everyday city life.

00:01:32.000 --> 00:02:00.000
NIA PATEL: Patience is everything
in wildlife cinematography.
You can wait hours, sometimes days,
for a single shot.

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:20.000
But when it happens—when you capture
that perfect moment of a predator hunting
or a bird taking flight—it's pure magic.

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:45.000
NARRATOR: Nia has traveled to six continents
documenting endangered species and ecosystems,
using her cinematography to raise awareness
about conservation.

00:02:45.000 --> 00:03:05.000
SARAH KIM: Diversity behind the camera
is just as important as diversity in front of it.
When creators from different backgrounds tell stories,
we get a richer, more complete picture of the world.
